The paper discusses the use of memristors as neuromorphic computing elements and their interface with neurons, which falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE) and emerging technologies (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the electrical properties of memristors, which could be classified under electromagnetics (cs.EM). The study of the interaction between the memristor network and the spiking neurons could also be considered a system-level analysis (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for direct communication between neurons and memristors, which could be relevant to computer communication (cs.CC).
